            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
            "@type": "School",
            "name": "Alpha International School - Sembakkam"
          },
          "author": {
            "@type": "Person",
            "name": "Praveen S"
          },
          "datePublished": "2021-04-22",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "4",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Studied from 2006 - 2016. In the early days, the school was small in both size and strength but being in school was great, the staffs, small playground, old office building and especially the fish tank in the entrance of the building where most of them will come and spend their time after the school is over. I even studied in a small building that was separate from the school building. Had a great time with the school till 9 std then the 10, 11 and 12 had a great time only because of my friends.\n\nWhen I was studying in 2016(12th) the old staff who taught me were almost gone from this school. This school doesn't pressure students to yield good academic results (don't know about now). In money wise school doesn't spend anything for students for eg: the school had once taken us to an exhibition, in the end, the school asked us to pay for the transportation.  In terms of what we pay as huge fees compared to other schools in the area, I think they can do better in these things. I even heard the pay for the teachers is also not so good.",
